    <briefdescription>
<para>Type trait to check if a type is nothrow-move-constructible. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Equivalent to std::is_nothrow_move_constructible. Uses the noexcept operator to detect whether Type&apos;s move constructor is noexcept.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Type</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The type to check</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
@SINCE_2_5.20</para>
<para>Example usage: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structDali_1_1IntegralConstant_1ab2bfc915a3437ec18d8b76f1fa516a88" kindref="member">IsNothrowMoveConstructible&lt;int&gt;::value</ref>;<sp/><sp/></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>true</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
